## Rules

1. Add one newest-first row and one concise entry during every v0.5.1 CLOSEOUT.
2. Link detailed evidence instead of copying it.
3. Record plan divergence, anomalies, and doctrine impact honestly; use `none`, `gap`, or `unknown` when appropriate.
4. Do not use this file to start work or silently change WORKSTREAMS status.
5. For same-branch multi-agent work, index unresolved attribution/diff gaps and preserve the branch/worktree until disposition.
6. Keep overall CLOSEOUT status separate from primary-main sync; main may sync successfully while attribution remains `partial-blocked`.
